  height: 400px;
  overflow-y: scroll;
  border: 1px solid #ccc;
  padding: 10px;
}

.message {
  margin-bottom: 10px;
}
```

### Step 6: Handle Cyberbullying and Harassment

To handle cyberbullying and harassment, you can add a simple filter to check for inappropriate words before adding a message to the state.

#### src/components/Chat.js (Updated)

```javascript
const inappropriateWords = ['badword1', 'badword2']; // Add more words as needed

const handleSendMessage = () => {
  if (newMessage.trim()) {
    const containsInappropriateWords = inappropriateWords.some((word) =>
      newMessage.includes(word)
    );

    if (containsInappropriateWords) {
      alert('Your message contains inappropriate language.');
    } else {
      dispatch(addMessage({ text: newMessage, user: user.name }));
      setNewMessage('');
    }
  }
};
```

### Conclusion

This guide provides a basic setup for a chat application with user profiles and message history, using Redux for state management and Bootstrap 4 for styling. It also includes a simple mechanism to handle cyberbullying and harassment by filtering inappropriate words. You can expand this further by adding more features and improving the UI/UX.
